.TH LU\-EXPAND 1 "2026-04-27" "logicutils 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lu\-expand \- combinatorial template expansion (Cartesian product)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lu\-expand
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fITEMPLATE\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lu\-expand
generates every combination of the supplied variable domains and
substitutes each combination into \fITEMPLATE\fR using the
.B {NAME}
placeholder syntax shared with
.BR lu\-match (1).

The order of the output corresponds to a multi\-digit odometer: the
last\-declared variable advances fastest.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-var \  "NAME=v1,v2,..."
Declare a variable and its inline value list. May be repeated.
.TP
.BI \-\-var\-file \  "NAME=PATH"
Declare a variable whose values are loaded from a file (one per line).
.TP
.BI \-\-filter= EXPR
Drop combinations that do not satisfy \fIEXPR\fR.
.TP
.BI \-\-sep= CHAR
Field separator for inline lists (default
.BR , ).
.TP
.BI \-\-format= FORMAT
Output format: \fIplain\fR, \fIjson\fR, \fItsv\fR, \fIcsv\fR, \fItoml\fR.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success, 2 on error.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Generate all alignment combinations except self\-alignments:
.PP
.RS
.nf
lu\-expand \-\-var \(aqS=s1,s2,s3\(aq \-\-var \(aqR=hg38,mm10\(aq \\\\
\(aqalign\-{S}\-{R}.bam\(aq
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lu\-match (1)
.SH AUTHOR
NEWSNIPER.
